  "conversations": [
    {
      "id": "thread_seed_global",
      "scope": "global",
      "ref": null,
      "messages": [
        {
          "id": "msg_seed_1",
          "role": "user",
          "content": "Beech stacking chair, mostly sound but with a hairline crack at the top of the front right leg, a worn seat (scuffs, stains, a scratch), a small dent in the backrest, and scuffs on the front left leg. I want to repair it in a way that lasts — and ideally makes the next repair easier too. Modern materials are fine if they're more durable.",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-14T09:45:00.000Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_seed_2",
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Good framing. The crack is the only structural concern — a low-viscosity wood epoxy will bond it back stronger than the surrounding fibres, and it lets us avoid removing material. The seat damage is all surface: a sand-back and a polyurethane finish will last far longer than the original lacquer. The dent and scuffs are minor, handled with steam and light sanding. One thing to flag: if we need to open the front right leg joint to clamp the crack properly, we could replace the glued dowels with M6 threaded inserts on reassembly — same strength, but the joint becomes serviceable. Worth doing on this chair?",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-14T09:45:30.000Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_seed_3",
          "role": "user",
          "content": "Yes — do the threaded inserts. And while we're at it, the plastic gliders are due for replacement; let's go with screw-on oak ones so they're user-replaceable in future.",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-14T09:46:00.000Z"
        },
        {
          "id": "msg_seed_4",
          "role": "assistant",
          "content": "Understood. Threaded inserts on the front right leg joint and oak screw-on gliders on all four legs. With those upgrades plus the crack repair, seat refinish, dent steaming, and leg sanding, I have what I need. Ready to generate the plan when you are.",
          "createdAt": "2026-05-14T09:46:30.000Z"
        }
      ],
      "createdAt": "2026-05-14T09:45:00.000Z"
    }
  ],
